Team Name
Backup

Automation Theme
Automated Backup Failure Detection and Incident Management

Problem Statement

* Cohesity provides native backup failure visibility through UI, alerts, and failure reports.
* These inputs still require operational correlation to identify which failures are currently unresolved.
* Failures need validation to confirm whether a later successful backup has cleared the issue.
* ServiceNow tracking also needs to be checked separately to avoid duplicate or missed incident handling.
* The challenge is not visibility alone; it is consolidated validation, incident tracking, and consistent follow-up for active backup failures.

Current Impact

* Backup alerts are received by email, but acting on every alert individually can create noise and duplicate checks.
* Some failures are cleared by later retries, so immediate incident updates without validation can be inaccurate.
* The team still needs to consolidate alerts, validate latest backup status, check ServiceNow, and track unresolved failures separately.
* This creates manual effort and possible detection gaps between scheduled reviews.

Proposed Automation Solution
Two interrelated controls support the same backup failure process.

1. Dynatrace Workflow – Scheduled Failure Detection and Incident Flow

* Uses a 24-hour backup failure compute window.
* Checks Cohesity backup failures using API-based logic.
* Validates whether each failure remains unresolved or is cleared by a later successful backup.
* Searches ServiceNow for the active backup failure incident.
* Creates one ServiceNow incident when unresolved backup failures are identified.
* Updates the same incident every 4 hours with the latest unresolved failure details.
* Sends email reports with current failure details for visibility and follow-up.
* Incident investigation, owner follow-up, remediation updates, and closure remain manual after operational review.

2. PowerShell Script – On-Demand Validation Flow

* Provides menu-driven validation for ad-hoc checks.
* Supports workload-specific execution for VM, SQL, Oracle, or All backup types.
* Supports multi-run validation depending on the selected workload scope.
* Supports verbose mode to show what the script is currently processing.
* Supports silent mode for quick validation output.
* Provides an interim validation control when email alerts indicate new failures or increased failure volume before the next Dynatrace update.

Why Immediate Action on Every Email Alert Is Not Always Practical

* Email alerts provide early notification, but they are not always consolidated with latest backup retry status.
* A failure may be cleared by a later successful backup, so validation is needed before incident updates.
* Dynatrace provides the structured incident workflow and recurring updates.
* PowerShell provides immediate ad-hoc validation when email alerts require faster confirmation.

Smart Control Logic

* The solution does not blindly report every backup failure.
* It checks whether a newer successful backup exists after the failure.
* Only unresolved failures are carried forward.
* Duplicate incident creation is avoided by updating the same active ServiceNow incident.
* Manual follow-up remains with the operations team for investigation, owner updates, remediation notes, and closure.

Tools Used
Dynatrace Workflow, Cohesity APIs, Dynatrace Credential Vault, ServiceNow Incident Integration, Email Alerts/Reports, PowerShell

